{
  "text": "Beech seedlings often undergo multiple suppression-and-release episodes before reaching the upper canopy [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Even after a long period of suppression, height growth increases following each canopy disturbance [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and particularly after the second and third release [CITATION_5] .",
